=== 10.5 The Matrix: Worked Example

Let `|V| = 5`, `d = 4`. Final hidden state:

----
h = [0.3, -0.1, 0.8, 0.2]
----

Unembedding matrix stem:[W_u = E^{\top}] (columns = token embeddings):

----
logits[0] = h · E[0] = (0.3)(0.10) + (-0.1)(−0.20) + (0.8)(0.30) + (0.2)(−0.40)
          = 0.030 + 0.020 + 0.240 − 0.080 = 0.210

logits[1] = h · E[1] = 0.150 − 0.060 − 0.560 + 0.160 = −0.310
logits[2] = h · E[2] = −0.270 − 0.010 + 0.160 − 0.060 = −0.180
logits[3] = h · E[3] = 0.120 + 0.050 + 0.480 − 0.140 = 0.510
logits[4] = h · E[4] = −0.030 − 0.080 − 0.320 + 0.100 = −0.330

logits = [0.210, -0.310, -0.180, 0.510, -0.330]
----

*Softmax:*

----
exp(logits) = [1.233, 0.733, 0.835, 1.665, 0.719]
sum         = 5.185

P = [0.238, 0.141, 0.161, 0.321, 0.139]
----

*Token 3 has the highest probability (32.1%)* — that's the model's best guess for next token.

Figure <<fig-ch10-matrix-projection>> shows the vocabulary projection converting a hidden state into logits over the vocabulary.
[[fig-ch10-matrix-projection]]
.Vocabulary projection
image::images/ch08_projection.png[Vocab projection — the unembedding matrix converts hidden states to logits over 50k tokens.]

Figure <<fig-ch10-matrix-generation>> shows autoregressive generation, where each predicted token is appended and fed back into the model.
